Australia's new prime minister: Your views
Julia Gillard has become Australia's first female prime minister after former PM Kevin Rudd stood aside from a party ballot.The ruling Labor Party has suffered a sharp drop in support in recent opinion polls.Mr Rudd's popularity plummeted following a number of policy setbacks.BBC News website readers in Australia have been commenting on the country's new leader.Read more of your comments